This operation verifies that a process with a particular PID exists

Inputs\:
	host\:            host name to check
	username\:        user name to login into host as
	password\:        password to use for login
	PID\:             the PID to check

Responses\:
	Running\:         If the process is running
	Not Running\:     If the process is not running
	Host Not Found\:  If the host cannot be found
	Authentication Failure\: If the login fails
	Failed\:          Any other error condition

Results and Context\:
	The ps return code is placed into the operation result
	Nothing is placed into the context
a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.3b5404e2-ca21-4112-89c9-e48fcd3fe86d.prompt=Now checking to see if the process is running, or if it has successfully terminated. a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.60c53b02-b81e-4317-bbd6-d08be1796b99.transition.description=The flow was unable to resolve the host name that the user entered a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.63abdd60-c614-432c-9783-f796da3a32be.prompt=password - password to use for login a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.787e35a2-d931-4f34-b1d1-a37557049384.prompt=Enter a value for username a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.7b5a9baa-3d72-46c4-9f34-e246754c353c.description=
This operation kills a process with extreme prejudice

Inputs\:
	host\:           host name to check
	username\:       user name to login into host as
	password\:       password to use for login
	PID\:            the PID of the process to kill

Responses\:
	Passed\:         If the file was deleted (return code was 0)
	Host Not Found\: If the host cannot be found
	Authentication Failure\: If the login fails
	Failed\:         Any other error condition

Results and Context\:
	The kill return code is placed into the operation result
	Nothing is placed into the context
a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.7b5a9baa-3d72-46c4-9f34-e246754c353c.prompt=Demonstrates how to kill processes with extreme prejudice. a0fad8a2-6d5c-4d08-8e9d-b080fb08de95.94248ca4-a3ae-4e3f-92a9-87f2818d9a10.description=
Sleeps the flow for the specified amount of seconds.

Input Parameters\:
seconds - the number of seconds to sleep

Responses\:
success - the number of seconds has elapsed
